comment: Holiday (NYK) legally contests Crawford's (LAC) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
[Observable in enhanced video] Anthony (NYK) moves his pivot foot.
Griffin (LAC) sets the screen on Holiday (NYK) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Porzingis (NYK) sets the screen on Rivers (LAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact. The contact following the screen is marginal.
Jordan (LAC) makes contact to Rose's (NYK) face during his drive to the basket.
Anthony (NYK) sets the screen on Rivers (LAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of a 3pt field goal is confirmed.
Rose (NYK) makes incidental contact with Rivers (LAC) that does not affect his SQBR.
Rose (NYK) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Rivers (LAC) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Griffin (LAC) makes contact with Porzingis' (NYK) arm that affects his shot attempt.
Holiday (NYK) commits a take foul on Jordan (LAC).
Anthony (NYK) and Griffin (LAC) face up and engage with one another but separate after the rebound.
Rivers (LAC) makes contact to Porzingis' (NYK) arm as he attempts to tip the rebound in.
Anthony (NYK) commits a take foul on Griffin (LAC).
